{
  "texts": [
    "Lastly, there is a need for a more standardized evaluation and classification of fairness methodologies from the perspective of their addressed fairness issues.",
    "Most reviews classify fairness-ensuring methodologies based on when the researchers are incorporating a bias mitigation strategy (Prior to the model implementation, after the model implementation, or during the model implementation).",
    "We need to connect these fairness-ensuring methodologies with the specific issue types.",
    "Emerging academics often require more direction for understanding a classification of methodologies from the perspective of specific fairness issues they solve.",
    "Researchers often adhere to conventional methodologies when addressing specific challenges in their field."
  ]
}